# E2E testing — ConciergeTravel.fr

## Strategy

- Three rings:
  1. **Unit** (Vitest) — pure domain logic + integration packages with MSW.
  2. **Integration** (Vitest + MSW) — vendor clients hitting mocked HTTP.
  3. **E2E** (Playwright) — every user journey that affects revenue or compliance.

A new business rule **must** add at least one unit test in `packages/domain/`.
A new user journey (booking, search, account, comparator) **must** add a Playwright spec.

## Test seams (dev-fake modules)

When an E2E flow depends on a vendor (Amadeus, Makcorps, Algolia, Supabase…), we ship **environment-gated test seams**.

- Modules live next to the consumer code as `dev-fake-<thing>.ts`.
- They are gated by env flags (`CCT_E2E_FAKE_HOTEL_ID`, `CCT_E2E_FAKE_PAID_HOTEL_ID`, …).
- The flag is the only way to activate them: production code paths must never branch on `NODE_ENV === 'test'`.
- Document each new seam in `docs/adr/0006-e2e-test-seams.md` (or add a successor ADR).

```ts
// ✅ Good — gated by an explicit opt-in env flag
if (isFakeOffersEnabled()) {
  return synthFakeOffer(input);
}

// ❌ Bad — would silently fake in production
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'test') { … }
```

## Playwright conventions

- Tests live in `apps/web/e2e/<journey>.spec.ts`. One spec file per journey.
- Use **role-based queries** (`page.getByRole('button', { name: /réserver/i })`) over CSS selectors.
- Always include an **accessibility assertion** (axe scan) on the rendered page before exiting.
- Test in **both locales** when the spec exercises locale-specific copy.
- Set `CCT_DISABLE_RATE_LIMITS=1` in the test env so rate limiters don't flake.

## CI

- Playwright browsers cached in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.
- E2E job runs after lint + typecheck + unit — fail fast on cheap signals.
- Long-running tests get `test.slow()`; the suite must stay under 5 min wall-clock.

See `.cursor/skills/test-strategy/SKILL.md`.
